The paper deals with designing a distributed coin-tossing protocol and analyzing its security against adversaries. This involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also uses martingales, which are a mathematical concept related to probability theory and stochastic processes, making it relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
